[SN]TITLE[SN]
Elite League: Giants exit play-offs after Panthers defeat

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Belfast Giants were beaten 3-1 by Nottingham Panthers in the play-offs quarter-final second leg to lose out 7-4 on aggregate.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is not supported on this device
Nottingham went into the SSE Arena game with a narrow advantage and Andy Bohmback extended their lead at the end of the first period.
Goals from Evan Mosey and Chris Lawrence made it 3-0.
Colin Shields netted a late consolation in what was a disappointing finish to the season for the Giants.
The Panthers will now take on Fife Flyers in the play-offs semi-finals at the National Ice Centre on Saturday.
